cat > /tmp/run-macro-tests.lisp << 'EOF'
(ql:quickload :alexandria :silent t)
(ql:quickload :rove :silent t)

(load #P"src/clysm/package.lisp")
(load #P"src/clysm/compiler/transform/macro.lisp")
(load #P"src/clysm/lib/macros.lisp")

;; Load test packages
(defpackage #:clysm/tests/unit/macro
  (:use #:cl #:rove))

(defpackage #:clysm/tests/unit/backquote
  (:use #:cl #:rove))

(in-package #:clysm/tests/unit/macro)

(format t "~%=== Running Macro Unit Tests ===~%")

;; Test macro registry
(deftest macro-registry
  (testing "register macro function"
    (let ((registry (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:make-macro-registry)))
      (ok (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:registry-p registry))))
  (testing "add macro to registry"
    (let ((registry (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:make-macro-registry)))
      (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
       registry 'test-macro (lambda (form) form))
      (ok (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macro-function* registry 'test-macro)))))

;; Test expansion depth limit
(deftest expansion-depth-limit
  (testing "infinite macro expansion triggers error"
    (let ((registry (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:make-macro-registry)))
      (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:register-macro
       registry 'infinite-loop
       (lambda (form) (declare (ignore form)) (list 'infinite-loop)))
      (ok (signals clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macro-expansion-depth-exceeded
            (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macroexpand* registry '(infinite-loop)))))))

;; Test case macro
(deftest case-macro
  (testing "case expands to let with conditionals"
    (let ((registry (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:make-macro-registry)))
      (clysm/lib/macros:install-standard-macros registry)
      (let ((expanded (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macroexpand* registry '(case x (a 1) (b 2)))))
        (ok (eq (first expanded) 'let))))))

;; Test prog1/prog2
(deftest prog-macros
  (testing "prog1 expands correctly"
    (let ((registry (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:make-macro-registry)))
      (clysm/lib/macros:install-standard-macros registry)
      (let ((expanded (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macroexpand* registry '(prog1 a b c))))
        (ok (eq (first expanded) 'let)))))
  (testing "prog2 expands correctly"
    (let ((registry (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:make-macro-registry)))
      (clysm/lib/macros:install-standard-macros registry)
      (let ((expanded (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macroexpand* registry '(prog2 a b c))))
        (ok (eq (first expanded) 'progn))))))

;; Test do/do*
(deftest do-macros
  (testing "do expands to block"
    (let ((registry (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:make-macro-registry)))
      (clysm/lib/macros:install-standard-macros registry)
      (let ((expanded (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macroexpand*
                       registry '(do ((i 0 (1+ i))) ((>= i 10))))))
        (ok (eq (first expanded) 'block)))))
  (testing "do* expands to block"
    (let ((registry (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:make-macro-registry)))
      (clysm/lib/macros:install-standard-macros registry)
      (let ((expanded (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macroexpand*
                       registry '(do* ((i 0 (1+ i))) ((>= i 10))))))
        (ok (eq (first expanded) 'block))))))

;; Test global macroexpand
(deftest global-macroexpand
  (testing "global registry exists"
    (ok (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:registry-p
         (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:global-macro-registry))))
  (testing "macroexpand-1 works"
    (clysm/lib/macros:install-standard-macros
     (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:global-macro-registry))
    (let ((expanded (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macroexpand-1 '(when t x))))
      (ok (eq (first expanded) 'if)))))

;; Run all tests
(rove:run-suite :clysm/tests/unit/macro)
EOF
sbcl --noinform --non-interactive --load /tmp/run-macro-tests.lisp 2>&1

## Implementation Summary for Phase 8 (016-macro-system)

Successfully implemented:

**1. Core Macro System (US1)**
- `macro-registry` structure for storing macros
- `register-macro` for adding macros
- `macroexpand-1*` and `macroexpand*` for expansion
- `*macro-expansion-limit*` to prevent infinite loops
- `macro-expansion-depth-exceeded` condition

**2. Backquote System (US2)**
- `expand-backquote` for quasiquote expansion
- Support for `,` (unquote) and `,@` (unquote-splicing)
- Nested backquote handling

**3. Standard Macros (US3-US4)**
- `when`, `unless`, `cond`, `case`
- `and`, `or`
- `prog1`, `prog2`
- `do`, `do*`
- `dolist`, `dotimes`

**4. User-facing API (US5)**
- `macroexpand-1` and `macroexpand` with global registry
- `global-macro-registry` and `reset-global-macro-registry`

**5. Defmacro Support (US1)**
- `parse-defmacro` for parsing defmacro forms
- `parse-lambda-list` with `&optional`, `&rest`, `&body`, `&key`, `&allow-other-keys`
- `compile-defmacro` for creating macro expanders
